.TH FASTFIND 1 "March 2026" "fastfind" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
fastfind - fast recursive file search tool

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fastfind
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIPATTERN\fR [\fIPATH\fR ...]

.B fastfind
"\fInatural language query\fR"

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fastfind
is a fast file searching tool designed for quickly locating files,
directories, and code symbols. It supports glob patterns, regular
expressions, fuzzy matching, and content searching.

Results can be filtered by file type, size, time, and Git status.
Commands may also be executed for each match using the
.B --exec
option.

.SH PATTERN MODES
.TP
.B --glob
Match using glob patterns (default).

.TP
.B --regex
Match using regular expressions.

.TP
.B --fixed
Literal substring match.

.TP
.B --fuzzy
Fuzzy matching against filenames.

.TP
.B --name
Match against basename only (default).

.TP
.B --full-path
Match against the full file path.

.TP
.B -i, --ignore-case
Case insensitive matching.

.TP
.B --smart-case
Case insensitive unless the pattern contains uppercase characters.

.SH TRAVERSAL
.TP
.B -H, --hidden
Include hidden files.

.TP
.B -L, --follow
Follow symbolic links.

.TP
.B -x, --one-file-system
Do not cross filesystem boundaries.

.TP
.B --gitignore
Respect .gitignore rules.

.TP
.B --min-depth N
Minimum traversal depth.

.TP
.B --max-depth N
Maximum traversal depth.

.TP
.B -j, --threads N
Number of parallel search threads.

.SH FILTERS
.TP
.B -t, --type TYPE
Filter by type: f (file), d (directory), l (symlink).

.TP
.B --size EXPR
Filter by file size (e.g. >10M, 10K..5M).

.TP
.B --newer TIME
Only files newer than the given timestamp.

.TP
.B --older TIME
Only files older than the given timestamp.

.TP
.B --changed DUR
Files modified within the given duration.

.TP
.B --recent
Files modified within the last 24 hours.

.TP
.B --contains TEXT
Search file contents for TEXT.

.TP
.B --exclude PATTERN
Exclude paths matching the pattern.

.SH GIT FILTERS
.TP
.B --git-modified
Show only modified files.

.TP
.B --git-untracked
Show only untracked files.

.TP
.B --git-tracked
Show only tracked files.

.TP
.B --git-changed
Show modified or untracked files.

.SH CODE SEARCH
.TP
.B --function NAME
Find function definitions matching NAME.

.TP
.B --class NAME
Find class definitions matching NAME.

.TP
.B --symbol NAME
Find symbol definitions.

.SH OUTPUT
.TP
.B -l, --long
Show extended file information.

.TP
.B --json
Output results as JSON.

.TP
.B --absolute
Print absolute paths.

.TP
.B --sort KEY
Sort results by path, name, size, or time.

.TP
.B -r, --reverse
Reverse sort order.

.TP
.B --limit N
Limit the number of results.

.TP
.B -c, --count
Only print the number of matches.

.TP
.B --stats
Display search statistics.

.TP
.B --exec CMD
Execute a command for each match. The placeholder
.B {}
is replaced with the file path.

.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
.TP
.B --interactive
Start a live interactive search interface.

.TP
.B --select
Interactively select results.

.SH INDEX
.TP
.B --use-index
Search using a cached index.

.TP
.B --rebuild-index
Rebuild the index.

.TP
.B --index-status
Show index information.

.SH MISC
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show help.

.TP
.B --version
Show version information.

.TP
.B -v, --verbose
Verbose output.

.TP
.B -q, --quiet-errors
Suppress error messages.

.SH EXAMPLES
Find Rust files in a source directory (use ff, or fastfind depending on what you have it under):

.nf
fastfind "*.rs" src/
.fi

Search for files containing TODO:

.nf
fastfind --contains "TODO"
.fi

Execute a command on each match:

.nf
fastfind "*.log" --exec "gzip {}"
.fi

Find recently modified files:

.nf
fastfind --recent
.fi

Search for a function definition:

.nf
fastfind --function main
.fi

Use fuzzy matching:

.nf
fastfind --fuzzy config
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
fd(1), rg(1), find(1)

.SH AUTHOR
Robert Flexx
